trans-unit.source: Auto_mkindex parses the Tcl scripts by sourcing them into a slave interpreter and monitoring the proc and namespace commands that are executed. Extensions can use the (undocumented) auto_mkindex_parser package to register other commands that can contribute to the auto_load index. You will have to read through auto.tcl to see how this works.
trans-unit.target: Auto_mkindex通过将Tcl脚本提供给从属解释器并监视执行的proc和命名空间命令来解析Tcl脚本。扩展可以使用（未​​记录）auto_mkindex_parser包来注册其他可能有助于auto_load索引的命令。您将必须通读auto.tcl以了解其工作原理。

trans-unit.source: Auto_mkindex_old (which has the same syntax as auto_mkindex) parses the Tcl scripts in a relatively unsophisticated way: if any line contains the word “proc” as its first characters then it is assumed to be a procedure definition and the next word of the line is taken as the procedure's name. Procedure definitions that do not appear in this way (e.g. they have spaces before the proc) will not be indexed. If your script contains “dangerous” code, such as global initialization code or procedure names with special characters like $, *, [ or ], you are safer using auto_mkindex_old.
trans-unit.target: Auto_mkindex_old（具有与auto_mkindex相同的语法）以相对不复杂的方式解析Tcl脚本：如果任何行的首字符包含单词“ proc ”，则假定它是过程定义，而该行的下一个单词是作为过程的名称。不会以这种方式出现的过程定义（例如，在proc之前有空格）将不会被索引。如果您的脚本包含“危险”代码，例如全局初始化代码或带有$，*，[或]等特殊字符的过程名称，则使用auto_mkindex_old会更安全。

trans-unit.source: Chan copy obeys the encodings and character translations configured for the channels. This means that the incoming characters are converted internally first UTF-8 and then into the encoding of the channel chan copy writes to (see chan configure above for details on the -encoding and -translation options). No conversion is done if both channels are set to encoding binary and have matching translations. If only the output channel is set to encoding binary the system will write the internal UTF-8 representation of the incoming characters. If only the input channel is set to encoding binary the system will assume that the incoming bytes are valid UTF-8 characters and convert them according to the output encoding. The behaviour of the system for bytes which are not valid UTF-8 characters is undefined in this case.
trans-unit.target: Chan copy遵循为通道配置的编码和字符翻译。这意味着，输入的字符被转换内部第一UTF-8，然后进入通道的编码瓒复制写入（参见陈配置上述的细节-encoding和-translation选项）。如果两个通道都设置为二进制编码并且具有匹配的转换，则不进行任何转换。如果仅将输出通道设置为编码二进制，则系统将写入传入字符的内部UTF-8表示形式。如果仅将输入通道设置为编码二进制系统将假定传入的字节是有效的UTF-8字符，并根据输出编码对它们进行转换。在这种情况下，未定义系统对于无效UTF-8字符字节的行为。

trans-unit.source: Pkg_mkIndex depends on the package unknown command, the package ifneeded command, and the auto-loader. The first time a package require command is invoked, the package unknown script is invoked. This is set by Tcl initialization to a script that evaluates all of the pkgIndex.tcl files in the auto_path. The pkgIndex.tcl files contain package ifneeded commands for each version of each available package; these commands invoke package provide commands to announce the availability of the package, and they setup auto-loader information to load the files of the package. If the -lazy flag was provided when the pkgIndex.tcl was generated, a given file of a given version of a given package is not actually loaded until the first time one of its commands is invoked. Thus, after invoking package require you may not see the package's commands in the interpreter, but you will be able to invoke the commands and they will be auto-loaded.
trans-unit.target: Pkg_mkIndex取决于程序包未知命令，程序包ifneeded命令和自动加载程序。第一次调用软件包require命令时，将调用软件包未知脚本。这是通过Tcl初始化设置为脚本的，该脚本评估auto_path中的所有pkgIndex.tcl文件。在将pkgIndex.tcl文件包含包ifneeded每个可用包的每个版本的命令;这些命令调用程序包提供命令以声明程序包的可用性，并且它们设置自动加载程序信息以加载程序包文件。如果-lazy在生成pkgIndex.tcl时提供了该标志，直到第一次调用其命令之一时，才实际加载给定软件包的给定版本的给定文件。因此，在调用软件包要求之后，您可能在解释器中看不到软件包的命令，但是您将能够调用这些命令并将它们自动加载。

trans-unit.source: Tclsh is a shell-like application that reads Tcl commands from its standard input or from a file and evaluates them. If invoked with no arguments then it runs interactively, reading Tcl commands from standard input and printing command results and error messages to standard output. It runs until the exit command is invoked or until it reaches end-of-file on its standard input. If there exists a file .tclshrc (or tclshrc.tcl on the Windows platforms) in the home directory of the user, interactive tclsh evaluates the file as a Tcl script just before reading the first command from standard input.
trans-unit.target: Tclsh是一个类似于shell的应用程序，它从其标准输入或文件中读取Tcl命令并对其进行评估。如果不带任何参数调用，它将以交互方式运行，从标准输入读取Tcl命令，并将命令结果和错误消息打印到标准输出。它会一直运行到调用exit命令或到达标准输入的文件末尾为止。如果用户的主目录中存在文件.tclshrc（或Windows平台上的tclshrc.tcl），则交互式tclsh会在从标准输入读取第一个命令之前将文件评估为Tcl脚本。

A namespace can also have child namespaces within it, so one library can contain its own private copy of many other libraries. A namespace can also be used to wrap up a group of related classes. trans-unit.source: [incr Tcl] provides object-oriented extensions to Tcl, much as C++ provides object-oriented extensions to C. The emphasis of this work, however, is not to create a whiz-bang object-oriented programming environment. Rather, it is to support more structured programming practices in Tcl without changing the flavor of the language. More than anything else, [incr Tcl] provides a means of encapsulating related procedures together with their shared data in a namespace that is hidden from the outside world. It encourages better programming by promoting the object-oriented "library" mindset. It also allows for code re-use through inheritance.
trans-unit.target: [incr Tcl]提供了对Tcl的面向对象的扩展，就像C ++提供了对C的面向对象的扩展一样。但是，这项工作的重点不是创建一个狂热的面向对象的编程环境。而是要在Tcl中支持更结构化的编程实践，而不改变语言的风格。更重要的是，[增量的Tcl]提供封装相关程序，在从外部世界隐藏着一个名称空间中的共享数据一起的一种手段。它通过促进面向对象的“库”思维方式来鼓励更好的编程。它还允许通过继承重用代码。

trans-unit.source: [incr Tk] is a framework for building mega-widgets. It uses [incr Tcl] to support the object paradigm, and adds base classes which provide default widget behaviors. See the itk man page for more details.
trans-unit.target: [incr Tk]是用于构建大型小部件的框架。它使用[incr Tcl]支持对象范例，并添加提供默认窗口小部件行为的基类。有关更多详细信息，请参见itk手册页。

trans-unit.source: [incr Widgets] is a library of mega-widgets built using [incr Tk]. It contains more than 30 different widget classes that can be used right out of the box to build Tcl/Tk applications. Each widget class has its own man page describing the features available.
trans-unit.target: [incr Widgets]是使用[incr Tk]构建的大型小部件的库。它包含30多种不同的窗口小部件类，可以直接使用它们来构建Tcl / Tk应用程序。每个窗口小部件类都有自己的手册页，描述了可用的功能。

trans-unit.source: exec will not work well with TUI applications when a console is not present, as is done when launching applications under wish. It is desirable to have console applications hidden and detached. This is a designed-in limitation as exec wants to communicate over pipes. The Expect extension addresses this issue when communicating with a TUI application.
trans-unit.target: 当不存在控制台时，exec不能与TUI应用程序一起正常工作，就像在wish下启动应用程序时一样。希望隐藏和分离控制台应用程序。这是设计上的限制，因为exec希望通过管道进行通信。与TUI应用程序通信时，Expect扩展解决了此问题。
